Hello Parent_E—thank you for reaching out. We’d be very happy to consider your family, and I’m glad Nursery_E is on your list.

**Start date flexibility:** We can typically accommodate the standard start at the beginning of the term, and we may be able to adjust within a reasonable window (e.g., a few weeks earlier/later) depending on staffing and onboarding. If you share your ideal start date, I can tell you what’s feasible.

**Daily schedule / hours:** Our day follows a consistent routine (arrival/settling-in, play-based learning blocks, outdoor time, lunch, rest/quiet time, afternoon activities, pick-up). Exact hours can vary by program, so please tell me the age group and whether you need full-day vs. shorter hours, and I’ll confirm the closest fit.

**Key requirements / documents:** We generally ask for a completed application form, proof of child’s age/identity, immunization/health records as required, emergency contacts, and any relevant care plans/allergies information. If your child has any specific needs or allergies, it’s helpful to flag that early so we can plan appropriately.

**Will the single spot fill quickly?** It may—because we have only one place, we expect decisions to move quickly once families begin submitting formal applications.

If Nursery_E is a serious option for you, I recommend submitting an **[APPLY]** as soon as you’re comfortable. To help you decide today, could you share (1) your child’s age, (2) desired start date, and (3) the schedule you need (full-day/part-day)?
